article.headline: Long Island U. 76, New Hampshire 72
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow. Long Island U. 76, New Hampshire 72. NEW YORK -- Kyle Johnson had 18 of his 25 points in the second half and Long Island University held off New Hampshire 76-72 on Saturday. Jaytornah Wisseh and Julian Boyd each added 10 points for the Blackbirds (3-5), who led 34-29 at halftime. Alvin Abreu had 18 points for the Wildcats (3-5), while Tyrece Gibbs added 15. A layup by David Hicks gave New Hampshire its last lead at 16-15. The Blackbirds then went on a 10-0 run that was capped by a layup by Johnson and they never trailed again.
